# EAS-specific ignore file. Shrinks the project archive that
# `eas build --local` uploads to the build server by excluding paths
# that apps/mobile doesn't depend on at install or runtime.
#
# Uses .gitignore syntax; honored by eas-cli's project-archive step.
#
# Why this matters: the first mobile dev APK build (2026-04-11) spent
# ~2-3 minutes in INSTALL_DEPENDENCIES compiling native modules from
# apps/desktop's Tauri stack — better-sqlite3 (node-gyp rebuild),
# esbuild × 3 versions, msgpackr-extract, etc. None of those end up
# in the mobile APK because Metro only bundles what's reachable from
# apps/mobile/src/**, but pnpm's frozen-lockfile install hydrates the
# entire workspace graph and runs every postinstall.
#
# Dropping apps/desktop from the tarball removes it from pnpm's
# workspace resolution on the builder, which skips all of those
# native compiles.
#
# Kept (NOT excluded):
#   apps/mobile/            — the app being built
#   packages/store/         — @vex-chat/store workspace runtime dep
#   packages/ui/            — kept for safety (tiny footprint; excluding
#                             might confuse pnpm's workspace resolver
#                             if the lockfile references it)
#   packages/eslint-config/ — devdep, pnpm lockfile references it
#   pnpm-workspace.yaml, pnpm-lock.yaml, package.json (root)
#   tsconfig.json, .tool-versions, .nvmrc (root build config)
#
# Excluded:

# ── Biggest win: desktop app's native dep chain ────────────────────────
apps/desktop/

# ── Non-build top-level directories ────────────────────────────────────
.github/
.beads/
scripts/
docs/
.verdaccio/

# ── Doc files at any depth ─────────────────────────────────────────────
*.md
